* She froze when the door before her began moving, half bewildered at the 
action but knowing by its senses that there was something edible on the 
other side.
In the back of her mind, Iron Raptors thoughts literally screamed to be 
heard, to take command of the body again, but the merged beast modes 
instincts and senses were too strong. It swamped them out and merged them 
with it's own mind to the point that she knew what she was doing and could 
coltrole it, but turned the thoughts feral so that she was running in 
instict rather then sheer thought.

The door continued to slide open, however, slowly.
But she wanted out, and now.
With a heave of her body, she had already slammed her snout towards the 
door, buckling it. With a flick of her head and twist of her neck, the door 
snapped off easily and flew across the room...only to slam against the far 
wall.
So, now she stood, braced on all fours and looking at something she hadn't 
expected to see there...Prowl.
In the back of her mind she slightly remembered him, his name...but barely 
anything else.
She fluidly walked slowly out of the small bathroom, now to tiny to hold her 
size comfortably for lone.
The mode continued to move from the room until her body was completely 
visable, her eyes locked on the bot as she moved, glaring at him as acidic 
saliva dripped from her parted lips...reviling sharp and jagged teeth.
And there she stopped, staring and glaring...muscles tense and tail 
thrashing...prey in sight....*
